    "date": "2017-08-11",
    "comment": "Rationale: Authors generated a specific antibody against calcineurin gamma which they used for studying the cellular localization of the protein. Coimmunostaining of primary hippocampal neurons reveals colocalization of CNA gamma with the glutamatergic presynaptic marker VGlut, which suggest the presence of CNA gamma in glutamatergic synapses. Subsequent pre-embedding immunoEM performed in hippocampal sections revealed CNA gamma immunoreactivity in the presynaptic compartment, in the vicinity of synaptic vesicles. This was supported by post-embedding immunogold EM, which also revealed the presence of the protein in the cytosol of the presynaptic compartment.. Experimental description: Fluoresence immunocytochemistry analysis of CNAgamma was performed on cultured rat hippocampal neurons.\nFor electron microscopy, vibratome sections from mouse hippocampi were used incubated with an anti-mouse CNA gamma antibody.\nFor antisera generation, human and mouse CNA gamma peptides were used.\n-Labeling of cultured rat hippocampal neurons was done with antibodies against rat CNA gamma (affinity purified antisera).",
